instructions:
## Set Up Tiptap v2 in Next.js (App Router)

### 1. Install packages
- Run: `npm install @tiptap/react @tiptap/pm @tiptap/starter-kit`
- For common extensions also install: `npm install @tiptap/extension-placeholder @tiptap/extension-character-count @tiptap/extension-link @tiptap/extension-image @tiptap/extension-text-align`
- Do NOT install `tiptap` (the legacy v1 package) — the current packages are scoped under `@tiptap/`.
- If using pnpm or yarn, use the equivalent commands.

### 2. Add ProseMirror base styles
- In your global CSS file (`app/globals.css` or equivalent), import ProseMirror styles:
  ```css
  @import '@tiptap/pm/style/pm.css';
  ```
- Alternatively, add a custom `.ProseMirror` block in your globals to style the editor area:
  ```css
  .ProseMirror {
    outline: none;
    min-height: 200px;
    padding: 0.5rem;
  }
  .ProseMirror p.is-editor-empty:first-child::before {
    color: #adb5bd;
    content: attr(data-placeholder);
    float: left;
    height: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  ```
- Missing ProseMirror styles causes broken list rendering and invisible cursor.

### 3. Create the editor component (Client Component)
- Tiptap uses browser APIs and must be a Client Component. Create `src/components/rich-text-editor.tsx`:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { useEditor, EditorContent } from '@tiptap/react';
  import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit';
  import Placeholder from '@tiptap/extension-placeholder';
  import CharacterCount from '@tiptap/extension-character-count';

  interface RichTextEditorProps {
    content?: string;
    onChange?: (html: string) => void;
    placeholder?: string;
    limit?: number;
  }

  export function RichTextEditor({ content = '', onChange, placeholder = 'Start writing...', limit = 10000 }: RichTextEditorProps) {
    const editor = useEditor({
      extensions: [
        StarterKit,
        Placeholder.configure({ placeholder }),
        CharacterCount.configure({ limit }),
      ],
      content,
      onUpdate: ({ editor }) => {
        onChange?.(editor.getHTML());
      },
      editorProps: {
        attributes: {
          class: 'prose max-w-none focus:outline-none min-h-[200px] p-2',
        },
      },
    });

    return (
      <div className="border rounded-md">
        <EditorContent editor={editor} />
        {limit && (
          <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground p-1 text-right">
            {editor?.storage.characterCount.characters()}/{limit}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
- `useEditor` returns `null` on the first server render — EditorContent handles this gracefully, but never access `editor` properties without a null check.

### 4. Toolbar component (optional)
- Add a formatting toolbar above EditorContent:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import type { Editor } from '@tiptap/react';

  interface ToolbarProps { editor: Editor | null; }

  export function Toolbar({ editor }: ToolbarProps) {
    if (!editor) return null;
    return (
      <div className="flex gap-1 border-b p-1 flex-wrap">
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleBold().run()} className={editor.isActive('bold') ? 'font-bold underline' : ''}>B</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleItalic().run()} className={editor.isActive('italic') ? 'italic underline' : ''}>I</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleBulletList().run()} className={editor.isActive('bulletList') ? 'underline' : ''}>• List</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleOrderedList().run()} className={editor.isActive('orderedList') ? 'underline' : ''}>1. List</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleHeading({ level: 2 }).run()} className={editor.isActive('heading', { level: 2 }) ? 'underline' : ''}>H2</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().toggleCodeBlock().run()} className={editor.isActive('codeBlock') ? 'underline' : ''}>Code</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().undo().run()} disabled={!editor.can().undo()}>↩</button>
        <button onClick={() => editor.chain().focus().redo().run()} disabled={!editor.can().redo()}>↪</button>
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
- The `editor.chain().focus()` pattern is required — never call commands without `.chain().focus()` or focus will be lost.

### 5. Loading saved content
- Pass existing HTML or JSON content to the `content` prop:
  ```tsx
  // From database (HTML string)
  <RichTextEditor content={post.body} onChange={setBody} />

  // From database (JSON object)
  <RichTextEditor content={JSON.stringify(post.bodyJson)} onChange={setBody} />
  ```
- To save as JSON (preserves structure better than HTML for re-editing):
  ```tsx
  onUpdate: ({ editor }) => {
    onChange?.(JSON.stringify(editor.getJSON())); // save as JSON
    // or
    onChange?.(editor.getHTML()); // save as HTML
  },
  ```
- HTML is easier for server-side rendering to display; JSON is better for re-editing.

### 6. Integrating with React Hook Form
- Use a controlled pattern with `setValue` and `Controller`:
  ```tsx
  import { Controller } from 'react-hook-form';

  <Controller
    name="body"
    control={control}
    render={({ field }) => (
      <RichTextEditor
        content={field.value}
        onChange={field.onChange}
      />
    )}
  />
  ```
- Do NOT pass `register()` directly to Tiptap — it only works with native inputs.

### 7. Image extension setup
- Add image support:
  ```tsx
  import Image from '@tiptap/extension-image';
  // In extensions array:
  Image.configure({ inline: false, allowBase64: true }),
  ```
- To insert an image: `editor.chain().focus().setImage({ src: url }).run()`
- For production, upload images to S3/Cloudflare R2 first, then insert the URL. Do NOT store base64 images in the database.

### 8. Link extension setup
- Add clickable links:
  ```tsx
  import Link from '@tiptap/extension-link';
  // In extensions array:
  Link.configure({ openOnClick: false, autolink: true }),
  ```
- To set a link: `editor.chain().focus().setLink({ href: 'https://example.com' }).run()`
- To remove: `editor.chain().focus().unsetLink().run()`

### 9. SSR / Next.js App Router considerations
- The `useEditor` hook uses browser APIs — it is fully safe in a `'use client'` component.
- If you must import the editor in a Server Component file for type purposes only, use `import type { Editor } from '@tiptap/react'` (type-only imports don't run in Node).
- Do NOT use `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })` unless you have a specific hydration mismatch you cannot fix otherwise — it causes layout shift.
- If you see hydration mismatches, check that the `content` prop is the same value on both server and client render. Pass `''` as default instead of `undefined`.

### 10. Displaying saved HTML (read-only)
- To display stored HTML outside the editor, use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with sanitization:
  ```tsx
  import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';
  <div
    className="prose max-w-none"
    dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: DOMPurify.sanitize(post.body) }}
  />
  ```
- Install DOMPurify: `npm install dompurify @types/dompurify`
- NEVER render unsanitized HTML from user input — this is an XSS vulnerability.
- Use Tailwind Typography (`@tailwindcss/typography`) for automatic prose styling: `npm install @tailwindcss/typography`.

### 11. Verify the integration
- Start the dev server: `npm run dev`.
- Type in the editor, apply bold/italic, create a list — verify formatting renders.
- Submit a form containing the editor and log the output — verify you get HTML or JSON as expected.
- Reload the page with pre-populated content — verify the editor shows saved content.
- Check the character count updates correctly.

### Common Errors
- **'document is not defined' or 'window is not defined'** — The editor component is missing `'use client'`. Add it as the first line of the file.
- **Lists or blockquotes render without styles** — ProseMirror CSS is not imported. Add `@import '@tiptap/pm/style/pm.css'` to globals.
- **Editor content resets on re-render** — You are passing a new `content` prop on every render. Tiptap does not sync external `content` changes after mount by default. Use `editor.commands.setContent(newContent)` imperatively if you must update content externally.
- **'useEditor is not a function'** — You installed the legacy `tiptap` package instead of `@tiptap/react`. Uninstall `tiptap`, install `@tiptap/react`.
- **Toolbar buttons lose editor focus** — Use `editor.chain().focus().toggleBold().run()` — the `.focus()` re-focuses the editor before executing the command.
- **Images stored as base64 inflate the database** — Configure your image extension to upload to storage first. Never allow base64 images to be saved to your database.
- **XSS vulnerability when rendering HTML** — Always sanitize HTML with DOMPurify before rendering with `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT install the legacy `tiptap` package — use `@tiptap/react`, `@tiptap/pm`, and `@tiptap/starter-kit`.
- Do NOT use `dynamic(..., { ssr: false })` by default — use `'use client'` instead. SSR-disable causes layout shift and is rarely necessary with Tiptap.
- Do NOT call `editor.getHTML()` or `editor.getJSON()` outside the `onUpdate` callback without a null check — `useEditor` returns null before mount.
- Do NOT store base64-encoded images in the database — always upload to object storage first.
- Do NOT render user-submitted HTML without DOMPurify sanitization — this is an XSS vulnerability.
- Do NOT pass `register()` from React Hook Form to the editor — use `Controller` with `onChange` instead.
- Do NOT use Tiptap for collaborative real-time editing without Yjs or Liveblocks — `useEditor` is not multiplayer-safe on its own.
